{"questionId":"9073658","questionHtml":"<p>The person must not slide down the wall. Show that the minimum angular velocity <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>ω</mi></math> of the cylinder for this situation is</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>ω</mi><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mi>g</mi><mrow><mi>μ</mi><mi>R</mi></mrow></mfrac></msqrt></math></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>μ</mi></math> is the coefficient of static friction between the person and the cylinder.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">See&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>F</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>μ</mi><mi>N</mi></math>&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><em><strong>AND</strong></em>&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>N</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>m</mi><mi>R</mi><msup><mi>ω</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle3\">✓</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle4\">«</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">substituting for N</span><span class=\"fontstyle4\">»&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>μ</mi><mi>m</mi><msup><mi>ω</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>R</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>m</mi><mi>g</mi></math>&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle3\">✓</span></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9073658","referenceCode":"20N.2.SL.TZ0.2b","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"The person must not slide down the wall. Show that the minimum angular velocity ω of the cylinder for this situation is ω=gμR where μ is the coefficient of static friction between ","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 6: Circular motion and gravitation","6.1 – Circular motion","Core","Topic 2: Mechanics","2.2 – Forces","Core","Topic 2: Mechanics","Core","Topic 6: Circular motion and gravitation"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders